About 30 firefighters were called out to tackle an overnight blaze at a pub in Cumbernauld, North Lanarkshire.
Crews were alerted to the fire at the the Kingfisher pub, in the town's Dowanfield Road, at about 01:10.
The incident commander brought in another three appliances after the first crew arrived to find flames coming from the roof of the building.
The fire service and Police Scotland will carry out a joint investigation to establish the cause of the fire.
